# Commit message subject line should be under 50 characters
# Commit message body line length should be wrapped at 72 characters

# Gitmoji is an emoji that represents the purpose of the commit.
# See https://gitmoji.dev/ for a full list of Gitmojis and their meanings.

# Type can be one of the following (with corresponding Gitmoji):
#   feat     (new feature)                                                                    :sparkles:
#   fix      (bug fix)                                                                        :bug:
#   refactor (refactoring code)                                                               :recycle:
#   style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)                           :art:
#   docs     (changes to documentation)                                                       :book:
#   test     (adding or refactoring tests; no production code change)                         :white_check_mark:
#   chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change)  :wrench:

# Scope is the part/module of the codebase affected by the change
# (optional; can be omitted for a small, general change)

